name: MetaMask Mobile

$ae_crashed_reason.description: The explanation of why the app crashed.

$ae_session_length.description: The number of seconds the user spent in the session.

$ae_total_app_session_length.description: The amount of time in seconds from when the user launches the app until the user stops using or leaves the app.

$ae_total_app_sessions.description: The total number of "App Session" events that the user has sent.

$android_app_version.description: The current android app version code

$android_brand.description: The brand of the Android device.

$android_lib_version.description: Version of the Mixpanel Android library used to send this data

$android_os_version.description: Current Android version for this device.

$app_build_number.description: The general build of this app.

$bluetooth_enabled.description: The Bluetooth app is enabled. Bluetooth icon is green when enabled and grey when not enabled.

$bluetooth_version.description: The version of the Bluetooth that is running on the device. Set to "none", "ble", or "classic".

$browser.description: The browser being used at the time the event was fired. (Not versioned)

$browser_version.description: The version number of the browser being used at the time the event was fired.

$carrier.description: The wireless carrier of the device owner.

$city.description: The city of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$country_code.description: The two-letter country code of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$current_url.description: The full URL of the webpage on which the event is triggered.

$device.description: The name of the event sender's device, if they're on mobile web.

$distinct_id.description: The way to uniquely identify your users. You can set this to any value using the identify method. Some Mixpanel libraries assign a random value by default.

$experiments.description: The list of all experiments and variants a user has been exposed to as a super property.

$failure_description.description: Mixpanel property explaining why an operation was not executed in detail

$failure_reason.description: Mixpanel property summarizing why an operation was not executed

$geo_source.description: Internal Mixpanel property to record the source used to determine location

$google_play_services.description: Whether Google Play Services is available or not in the device

$has_nfc.description: The Near Field Communication (NFC) is enabled. Set to true if Near Field Communication is being used, false if not.

$has_telephone.description: Verifies the mobile phone device is functional. Set to true if this device has telephone functionality, false if not.

$initial_referrer.description: The referring URL at first arrival.

$initial_referring_domain.description: The referring domain at first arrival.

$ios_device_model.description: The model ID of the device.

$ios_lib_version.description: The Mixpanel library that is used to send this data.

$ios_version.description: The current version of iOS on the device.

$lib_version.description: Version of the Mixpanel library used to enqueue or send this data.

$os.description: The operating system of the event sender.

$os_version.description: The current version of operating system on the device.

$radio.description: The current cellular network communication standard.

$referrer.description: The referring URL, including your own domain.

$referring_domain.description: The referring domain, including your own domain.

$region.description: The region (state or province) of the event sender that is parsed from IP.

$screen_dpi.description: The pixel density of the device screen.

$screen_height.description: The height of a device's screen.

$screen_width.description: The width of the screen of the device.

$search_engine.description: The search engine that was used to arrive at your domain.

$timezone.description: The timezone of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$transactions.description: The list with specially formatted JSON objects, one for each purchase or transaction associated with a specific profile.

$user_id.description: A default Mixpanel property to track the $identified_id passed into identify method client-side. Stored locally on the user's device using the register method.

$wifi.description: The wifi connectivity is enabled. Set to true if Wifi is connected, false if not.

mp_country_code.description: The country of the event sender, parsed from IP.

mp_sent_by_lib_version.description: Version of the Mixpanel library used to send this data over the network (not necessarily the same as the version which enqueued the data).

$android_brand.description: The brand of the Android device.

$bluetooth_enabled.description: The Bluetooth app is enabled. Bluetooth icon is green when enabled and grey when not enabled.

$browser.description: The browser being used at the time the event was fired. (Not versioned)

$carrier.description: The wireless carrier of the device owner.

$city.description: The city of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$country_code.description: The two-letter country code of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$current_url.description: The full URL of the webpage on which the event is triggered.

$device.description: The name of the event sender's device, if they're on mobile web.

$experiments.description: The list of all experiments and variants a user has been exposed to as a super property.

$failure_description.description: Mixpanel property explaining why an operation was not executed in detail

$failure_reason.description: Mixpanel property summarizing why an operation was not executed

$geo_source.description: Internal Mixpanel property to record the source used to determine location

$google_play_services.description: Whether Google Play Services is available or not in the device

$has_telephone.description: Verifies the mobile phone device is functional. Set to true if this device has telephone functionality, false if not.

$initial_referring_domain.description: The referring domain at first arrival.

$radio.description: The current cellular network communication standard.

$screen_height.description: The height of a device's screen.

$screen_width.description: The width of the screen of the device.

$search_engine.description: The search engine that was used to arrive at your domain.

$timezone.description: The timezone of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$transactions.description: The list with specially formatted JSON objects, one for each purchase or transaction associated with a specific profile.

$wifi.description: The wifi connectivity is enabled. Set to true if Wifi is connected, false if not.

$ios_device_model.description: The model ID of the device.

$ios_lib_version.description: The Mixpanel library that is used to send this data.

$ios_version.description: The current version of iOS on the device.

$lib_version.description: Version of the Mixpanel library used to enqueue or send this data.

$os.description: The operating system of the event sender.

$os_version.description: The current version of operating system on the device.

$radio.description: The current cellular network communication standard.

$referrer.description: The referring URL, including your own domain.

$referring_domain.description: The referring domain, including your own domain.

$region.description: The region (state or province) of the event sender that is parsed from IP.

$screen_dpi.description: The pixel density of the device screen.

$screen_height.description: The height of a device's screen.

$screen_width.description: The width of the screen of the device.

$search_engine.description: The search engine that was used to arrive at your domain.

$timezone.description: The timezone of the event sender, parsed from IP.

$transactions.description: The list with specially formatted JSON objects, one for each purchase or transaction associated with a specific profile.

$user_id.description: A default Mixpanel property to track the $identified_id passed into identify method client-side. Stored locally on the user's device using the register method.

$wifi.description: The wifi connectivity is enabled. Set to true if Wifi is connected, false if not.

mp_country_code.description: The country of the event sender, parsed from IP.

mp_keyword.description: The search keywords detected on the referrer from a search engine to your domain. This property is only collected when search keywords are included in a URL.

mp_lib.description: The name of the Mixpanel Library that sent the event.

mp_original_distinct_id.description: Original distinct id for an event that was identified as contributing to a hotshard.

mp_original_event_name.description: Original event name for an event that was identified as contributing to a hotshard.

mp_sent_by_lib_version.description: Version of the Mixpanel library used to send this data over the network (not necessarily the same as the version which enqueued the data).

utm_content.description: Identifies the exact element on your ad that was clicked. For example, if you have two call-to-actions within the same email message with one being a video_ad and another being a green_banner ad.

utm_medium.description: Identifies what type of link sent traffic.

utm_source.description: Identifies which site sent the traffic.
